The issue is now fixed. If you start your notebook with: 

!pip install git+https://github.com/autonomio/talos@daily-dev
!pip install git+https://github.com/mikkokotila/astetik

But note that you must have astetik v.1.9.7 ... for some reason I was able to achieve this only with the above code on colab, even though that's the current pypi version. So you might be able to just `pip install -U astetik` instead.

The issue was that Seaborn (which is underlying astetik which is the plot API for Talos) had moved colorbar related arguments from sns.kdeplot(). The v.1.9.7 version of astetik resolves that.
